metadata.name: The Tangled Poetess
metadata.description:
I weave day and night  
A heavy heart that burns  
Like the wick of a candle blazes  
To enlighten the saints

I am not an angel  
But a tangled dream  
I am not an angel  
But only your feelings

The threads of life are short  
I warned you once before  
See, as the hour draws near  
The shadows are fading

And while your eyes sing  
Your smile torments the mind  
As my name echoes forever  
In your breath
